 the construction of cores for those customers.  This is persuasively answered by Mr. Silva who argued that, in those cases, it was for the core and tube manufacturer to ensure that it produced a core of the requisite crush strength.  If the manufacturer a
ttempted to cut corners by under-specifying the crush strength the core would collapse, presumably together with the core manufacturer\'92s business.}}}
