at the merged entity would conduct business as usual.  There would seem to be little point in a vertical transaction between parties that did not have self-dealing as a central objective and post-merger feature. Certainly any efficiency gains to be derived
 from a vertical transaction would rely on self-dealing, on the internalization of transaction costs and other prospective efficiency rationales that potentially arise from vertical transactions. The US Courts simply presume that an \'91\'85integrated firm will 
deal with itself when all things are roughly equal as they usually will be.  Indeed, this would seem to the primary motive for vertical mergers.\'92{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s17{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 Areeda, Hovenkamp and Solow  op.cit. page 159}}}
{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af10\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af10\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\lang1033\f8\fs24\f8\lang1025\qj 63.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 However, just as self-dealing may be at the heart of efficiency gains, so may it be the centerpiece of anti-competitive foreclosure. The important question to be resolved by a competition evaluation of a vertical merger is usually whether the internalizati
on of trade that is implied by a vertical agreement is pro-competitive or competition neutral or whether it is anti-competitive.  In this transaction we have been offered nothing other than bland assertions regarding potential pro-competitive consequences 
\'96 not a shred of evidence has been presented to substantiate the sparse assertions of efficiency gains.  On the other hand, the post-merger market structure and the incentives of the key players persuade us that input foreclosure will be an outcome of the 
transaction with a consequent increase in the costs faced by both the downstream and the upstream rivals of the merged entity.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\lang1033\f8\fs24\f8\lang1025\qj 64.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 In summary, then we proceed on the basis \'96 in our estimation an eminently reasonable assumption \'96 that the post-merger integrated entity will largely self-deal, that is, it will largely confine its sales of Ndicore to its integrated downstream cores and tu
bes manufacturer and that the latter will largely confine its purchases of core board to its upstream producer of core board. Mondi\'92s integrated core board and cores and tubes producer will certainly engage in a {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i limited} amount of trade in the market.  As a
lready intimated (and elaborated more fully below) a limited amount of participation in the market will facilitate the flow of information, and, hence facilitate cooperation between Mondi and Sappi.  In addition it is probably unreasonable to expect a math
ematically precise alignment between the output of Ndicore by the upstream division and the demand for Ndicore by the downstream division. Mondi\'92s upstream division would enter the market to sell occasional supplies of Ndicore in excess of its needs and it
s downstream division would enter the market to make good occasional shortfalls in the supply of Ndicore.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s17{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 Ndicore is produced by a single machine at Mondi\'92s Springs plant.  This machine is, however, not dedicated to the production of Ndicore \'96 it is thus a relatively simple matter to increase the machine time devoted to Ndicore as per the requirements of the 
downstream cores and tubes division.  However relative to the alternative product which is produced by this machine, Ndicore is low margin.  Accordingly both commercial imperatives and, as will be elaborated below, Mondi\'92s monopolization strategy ensure th
at the output of Ndicore will be limited to the requirements of the downstream cores and tubes manufacturer. See pages 224 \'96 225 and 230 of the transcript. }}}
{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af10\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af10\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }       }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\lang1033\f8\fs24\f8\lang1025\qj 65.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Given then that the merged entity will largely self-deal, that is, it will, by and large, restrict sales of Ndicore to its downstream division alone, all other cores and tubes manufacturers will be left in the hands of an effective Sappi monopoly.  There w
ould, under these circumstances, be little to prevent Sappi from exercising its new found market power by charging a monopoly price for its core board, Spiralwind. To the extent that Mondi\'92s newly merged entity continues to participate in the market (that 
is, to the extent that it does {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i not }exclusively self-deal but rather continues to supply some Ndicore to non-integrated cores and tubes manufacturers) it will have no interest in increasing output and decreasing prices in order to wrest market share from it
s rival, Sappi. On the contrary Mondi\'92s best interests would simply lie in following Sappi\'92s price increase thus permitting both producers of core-board to extract monopoly rents from non-integrated cores and tubes manufacturers in the downstream market.  
Hence by reducing the supply of Ndicore to the market (that is by engaging largely in self-dealing) Mondi will permit Sappi to increase the price of core-board to non-integrated producers of cores and tubes.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s17{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 We do note however that, any anti-competitive imperatives aside, Mondi\'92s capacity to produce Ndicore is restricted to a single machine located at its Springs plant.  This machine is not dedicated to Ndicore and Mondi\'92s witness commented that it could be u
sed for the production of more commercially lucrative alternatives.  So, even from a narrow commercial perspective there is no incentive to increase the supply of Ndicore.}}}
{\*\cs58\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af10\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af10\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }  Sappi will be the principal beneficiary of thi
s strategy in the upstream market \'96 it will supply the lion\'92s share of this market and it will do so at a monopoly price.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\lang1033\f8\fs24\f8\lang1025\qj 66.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Mondi\'92s interest in allowing Sappi to charge a monopoly price to its customers resides in the impact of Sappi\'92s monopoly price in the downstream core and tube market \'96 it raises the cost of Mondi\'92s rivals in the downstream cores and tubes market thus eithe
r enabling Mondi\'92s newly acquired cores and tubes division to capture a larger share of this market, or, more rationally, enabling it to raise its prices to its customers in the downstream market, a market in which it will, through its acquisition of KC&T,
 already command a dominant share.  In this way vertical integration does indeed ensure that this will be good business opportunities for both Mondi and Sappi.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af8\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af8\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
